title: Printer's Sample Book, 1878–79
creditline: Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts
description: Small leather notebook with handwritten formulas for dyestuffs to be used for printed textiles. Contains 145 samples of printed fabric in a variety of patterns.

tombstone.epitaph:
Printer's Sample Book, 1878–79.
1878–79. Medium: leather, paper, cotton. Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts. 1945-55-33.
